{"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Building a macOS VM Manager","role":"collectionGroup"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BuildingAMacOSVMManager"},"abstract":[{"text":"Compose the Spooktacular libraries into a first-class Mac app.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This article walks through the layered structure of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Spooktacular SwiftUI app so you can build something comparable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"without repeating the architectural decisions we already settled.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The app target depends on three Swift packages in this repo:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SpookCore"}]},{"text":" — pure Swift domain types. No AppKit, no","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Virtualization","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", no networking. Use it for models, enums,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and protocol “ports” that describe what the app needs without","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"committing to a concrete transport.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookApplication","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":" — use cases and services that combine","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"domain types into workflows (RBAC evaluation, tenant","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"isolation, runner-pool orchestration).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookInfrastructureApple","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Apple-framework adapters.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Wraps ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZVirtualMachine"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSPasteboard","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSWorkspace","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Security.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Network.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Foundation Models"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Views stay thin: they observe ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" state objects and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call through to these libraries. Keeping logic out of views is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"what makes the same codebase ship a CLI, a Kubernetes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"controller, and an App Store binary from one package.","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"],"title":"Related Documentation"}],"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/buildingamacosvmmanager"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted","